rbian (the language of the 2007 winning song) are fully [[mutual intelligibility|mutually intelligible]] and often considered varieties of a single language, [[Serbo-Croatian]]. However, they are listed separately in Eurovision statistics.</ref>\n|[[Eurovision Song Contest 1989|1989]]\n|[[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|Yugoslavia]]\n|-\n|[[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]]\n|[[Eurovision Song Contest 2004|2004]]<ref group=\"N\" name=\"wilddances\">This song was partially sung in [[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]].</ref>\n|[[Ukraine]]<ref group=\"N\" name=\"wilddances\">This song was partially sung in [[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]].</ref>\n|-\n|[[Serbian language|Serbian]]<ref group=\"N\" name=\"serbo-croatian\">Croatian (the language of the 1989 winning song) and Serbian (the language of the 2007 winning song) are fully [[mutual intelligibility|mutually intelligible]] and often considered varieties of a single language, [[Serbo-Croatian]]. However, they are listed separately in Eurovision statistics.</ref>\n|[[Eurovision Song Contest 2007|2007]]\n|[[Serbia]]\n|-\n|[[Crimean Tatar language|Crimean Tatar]]\n|[[Eurovision Song Contest 2016|2016]]<ref group=\"N\" name=\"1944_(song)|1944\">This song was partially sung in [[Crimean Tatar language|Crimean Tatar]].</ref>\n|[[Ukraine]]<ref group=\"N\" name=\"1944_(song)|1944\">This song was partially sung in [[Crimean Tatar language|Crimean Tatar]].</ref>\n|-\n|[[Portuguese language|Portuguese]]\n|[[Eurovision Song Contest 2017|2017]]\n|[[Portugal]]\n|-\n|}\n\n== Photogallery ==\n<gallery class=\"center\" classes=\"center\">\nFile:Lys Assia (1957).jpg|[[Lys Assia]], winner of the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1956|1956]] contest for Switzerland.\nFile:Eurovision Song Contest 1958 - Corry Brokken.png|[[Corry Brokken]], winner of the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1957|1957]] contest for the Netherlands.\nFile:Eurovision Song Contest 1958 - Andr\u00e9 Claveau.png|[[Andr\u00e9 Claveau]], winner of the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1958|1958]] contest for France.\nFile:Dam tot Dam race , Teddy Scholten in aktie, Bestanddeelnr 910-6304.jpg|[[Teddy Scholten]], winner of the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1959|1959]] contest for the Netherlands.\nFile:Jacqueline Boyer (1960).jpg|[[Jacqueline Boyer]], winner of the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1960|1960]] contest for France.\nFile:Jean-Claude Pascal 1945.pdf|[[Jean-Claude Pascal]], winner of the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1961|1961]] contest for Luxembourg.\nFile:Isabelle Aubret.jpg|[[Isabelle Aubret]], winner of the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1962|1962]] contest for France.\nFile:J\u00f8rgen & Grethe Ingmann.jpg|[[J\u00f8rgen Ingmann|J\u00f8rgen]] & [[Grethe Ingmann]], winners of the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1963|1963]] contest for Denmark.\nFile:Gigliola Cinquetti (1966).jpg|[[Gigliola Cinquetti]], winner of the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1964|1964]] contest for Italy.\nFile:Eurovision Song Contest 1965 - France Gall.jpg|[[France Gall]], winner of the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1965|1965]] contest for Luxembourg.\nFile:Eurovision Song Contest 1965 - Udo J\u00fcrgens.jpg|[[Udo J\u00fcrgens]], winner of the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1966|1966]] contest for Austria.\nFile:Sandie Shaw 3.jpg|[[Sandie Shaw]], winner of the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1967|1967]] contest for the United Kingdom.\nFile:Spaanse zangeres Massiel, winnares Euro Song Festival tijdens opname in studio K, Bestanddeelnr 921-2648.jpg|[[Massiel]], winner of the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1968|1968]] contest for Spain.\nFile:Popzangeres Salome zal Spanje vertegenwoordigen op Euro Songfestival in Madrid, Bestanddeelnr 922-1722.jpg |[[Salom\u00e9 (singer)|Salom\u00e9]], one of the four winners of the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1969|1969]] contest for Spain.\nFile:Lulu (2010).jpg|[[Lulu (singer)|Lulu]], one of the four winners of the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1969|1969]] contest for the United Kingdom.\nFile:Nationale finale van het Eurovisie Songfestival in Scheveningen, Lenny Kuhr zong, Bestanddeel