s://www.facebook.com/thebirdsongs/photos/p.10162087383785231/10162087383785231/?type=1&theater</ref>\n\n==The Journey: Act I; The Beginning==\nThe Birdsongs released the first EP in a two-part project entitled \"The Journey: Act I; The Beginning\" on November 20, 2012. They started work on the project with [[Grammy Award|Grammy]]-nominated, [[GMA Dove Award|Dove Award]] winning producer [[Travis Wyrick]] ([[Pillar (band)|Pillar]], [[Disciple (band)|Disciple]], [[TobyMac]], [[P.O.D. (band)|P.O.D.]]) who also produced their radio singles. The band finished the EP in [[Nashville, Tennessee|Nashville]] with producer Geoff Hunker of the band [[Satellites & Sirens]] and producer/mixer Grant Craig who has worked with bands such as [[12 Stones]] and [[Egypt Central]]. \"The Journey: Act I; The Beginning\" includes the popular radio single \"Pieces (Hold On)\" in addition to their singles \"Will You Save Me?\" and \"This Isn't Love.\" This first EP is the first part of a two-part storyline. The story will culminate with a full-length LP \"The Journey: Act II; The War\" being released September 6th, 2019.\n\n== Singles ==\n* \"Pieces (Hold On)\" -  (#24 on ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' BDS National Christian Rock Airplay Chart - March 2010, #27 on [[ChristianRock.Net]]'s Top 100 of 2010, and #23 on their Top 100 Most Requested on 2010) <ref>http://www.christianrock.net/top2000.asp?year=2010</ref><ref>http://www.christianrock.net/mostrequested2000.asp?year=2010</ref>\n* \"So Much More\"\n* \"Will You Save Me?\" - (#23 on ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' BDS National Christian Rock Airplay Chart - September 2012, #1 on [[ChristianRock.Net]]'s Top 30 - December 2012-January 2013) <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.christianrock.net/charts.asp |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-02-21 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120219153023/http://www.christianrock.net/charts.asp |archivedate=February 19, 2012 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n* \"This Isn't Love\" - (#9 on ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' BDS National Christian Rock Airplay Chart - May 2014, #1 on [[ChristianRock.Net]]'s Top 30 - May 2014) <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.christianrock.net/charts.asp |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-02-21 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120219153023/http://www.christianrock.net/charts.asp |archivedate=February 19, 2012 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n* \"God Rest Ye Merry Gentleman\" - (#3 on Christian Music Weekly - 2016) <ref>http://christianmusicweekly.com/newface/index.php/2011-03-31-04-23-33/68-christmas/1704-1-4-christmas</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n*Celestial Stationary EP (2008, Independent)\n*The Journey: Act 1; The Beginning (2012, Independent)\n*How Great Thou Art: Hymns II (2016, Independent)\n*The Birdsongs' Tennessee Christmas (2017, Independent)\n*The Journey: Act II; The War (2019, Independent) \n\n==Members==\n'''Current members'''\n* Benjamin Birdsong - Lead Vocals, Guitar, Fiddle, Mandolin\n* Coleene Birdsong - Backing Vocals, Bass, Guitar, Fiddle\n* Timothy Birdsong - Keyboards, Backing Vocals, Guitar, Bass, Auxiliary Percussion \n* Philip Birdsong - Drums, Backing Vocals, Guitar\n'''Former members'''\n* Matthew Birdsong - Bass, Backing Vocals, Banjo, Fiddle\n* Wendell Birdsong - Guitar, Backing Vocals\n\n== References ==\n<!--- See [[Wikipedia:Footnotes]] on how to create references using <ref></ref> tags which will then appear here automatically -->\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://facebook.com/thebirdsongs Official Facebook]\n*[https://twitter.com/thebirdsongs Official Twitter]\n* [https://itunes.apple.com/us/artist/the-birdsongs/id350752364 iTunes]\n* [http://thebirdsongs.storenvy.com/ Online Store]\n* [http://vk.com/the_birdsongs#!/thebirdsongs Vk.com]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Birdsongs (Band)}}\n[[Category:Musical groups from Seattle]]\n", "name_user": "Lrstreet88", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eDiscography:separate Albums and EPs headings", "url_page"